Males: Fore femur, palar claw (
Fig. 20A
), median lobe of sternite VII, and free lobe (
Fig. 20B
) as in diagnosis of subgenus. Fore tibia with two spines ventrodistally. Left paramere: shaft stout, with knoblike apex; basal lobe tongue-shaped, directed towards apex of paramere (
Fig. 20D
). Right paramere: shaft relatively slender, curved at distal third, slightly widened, then tapering towards a narrowly rounded apex (
Fig. 20C
).

Vietnam : Hanoi , Quang Ninh , Ha Tinh ( Wróblewski 1962 , 1967 , as
M. punctata
); first records for Ninh Binh and southern provinces of Vietnam . Other countries: widespread from India and Sri Lanka through Southeast Asian mainland to Sumatra, Java, and Bali ( Nieser 2002b ).
